'''''Lucifer Rising''''' is an [[Extended play|EP]] released by the Swedish [[doom metal]] band [[Candlemass]] in 2008, on the label [[Nuclear Blast]]. Candlemass recorded two new tracks, "Lucifer Rising" and "White God," and re-recorded "Demons Gate" for this release.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.ultimate-guitar.com/news/upcoming_releases/candlemass_lucifer_rising_ep_in_october.html | title = Candlemass: 'Lucifer Rising' EP In October | date = 2008-08-07 | publisher = Ultimate Guitar | accessdate = 2009-02-03}}</ref> The collection is also primarily composed of a series of 9 live tracks recorded in Athens, Greece on their 2007 tour (sides 2 to 4 on the vinyl edition).<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.roadrunnerrecords.com/BLABBERMOUTH.NET/news.aspx?mode=Article&newsitemID=95754 | title = Candlemass: ''Lucifer Rising'' EP to Include Two New Tracks | date = 2008-04-06 | publisher = [[blabbermouth.net]] | accessdate = 2009-02-03}}</ref> Recording on the new material was completed in April 2008.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.metalmartyr.com/candlemass-lucifer-rising-ep-due-out-in-september/ | title = Candlemass Lucifer Rising Ep Due Out In September | date = 2008-04-28 | publisher = Metal Martyr | accessdate = 2009-02-03}}</ref>

